<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Harry1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Harry,</orth> another form of <cit><quote>Henry:</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 1</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 144</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.21" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.220.21" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 220</bibl> (Ff. <emph>Henry</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 24</bibl> etc. etc. <cit><quote>four H. ten shillings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.236" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 236</bibl></cit>, i. e. pieces of the value of ten shillings, coined by Henry VII, not by Henry IV.
